rComments: AMAZING! Although he can sometimes come off a bit cocky, he is very engaging and knowledgable. If you have the chance I highly recommend taking him. Read the texts before class (even a skim) and you'll get a lot more out of the lectures. His grading is a little harsher than I'm used to but very fair and he gives good feedback.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: Professor Paris succeeded brilliantly in sharing his passion with us and keeping the course interactive in a very difficult distance learning context. He is an enthusiastic guy and brought very interesting guests, so it is just impossible not to love his course. He cares a lot about his students. In a nutshell, it was awesome!
Very knowledgeable on international affairs and CFP. Quick grader. Gives good feedback. Exams are based on readings, no surprise.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I definitely recommend taking a class with Professor Paris. He cares about the success of his students, and is a fair marker. Although this class was basically a book club (200+ pages per week), the assigned readings were really interesting and covered a wide range of topics in international affairs. Be prepared to read ALOT, but also to learn lots
He's a really great professor. Very knowledgeable and approachable. I would definitely take a class with him again.

I highly recommend taking a course with Professor Paris. He is an extremely knowledgeable academic and has a ton of practical experience. Really good at facilitating and moderating class discussions. The course was like a book club (200 ish page book per week most weeks). Gives good feedback on assignments and is a fair marker.

Canadian Foreign Policy with Professor Paris was a treat of a class. His practical and academic experience made the class discussion extremely education and productive. In addition, he brought in fantastic guest speakers. He is also a very fair marker.
Professor Paris is an amazing professor. He does assign a lot of readings but they are generally enjoyable and his lectures are hilarious/educational. He is also an extremely fair marker.

Roland Paris is an excellent professor. I really enjoyed the practical nature of his course. We learned about IR theory by reading one book a week about real world issues from conflicting viewpoints. Even with his new appointment to the PM, he was very humble and kind to students!!! Made me respect him even more (and feel confident in PM JT).

Brilliant prof. Yes, you have to read a ton, but it's good for you. And I learned so much... I also find I really impress people with all the IR authors I can cite. He's really funny, he'll sing and dance, but so passionate about international affairs. Very inspiring.
The books ... Oh my God ... It is just too much : I mean like others a 200 pages novel by week ! During 9-10 weeks, it is just too much. He is an excellent scholar, but too hard with his readings

Prof. Paris has very high expectations. As in, reading a 200+ pg book/class. But, he is engaging, interesting, and just a really fun guy. His exams are difficult but he scales them it seems. Amazing prof if you're willing to put in the work. He's super busy but willing to help out in any way he can. Totally worth the challenge.

Toughest professor I've ever had. Ever. If you like reading and I mean 200+ pages PER WEEK then by all means take his class. If you're not that down with the subject material to begin with, prepare for a semester of wanting to blow your brains out.
Amazing professor all-round. The class wasn't that hard. Just do the work, read a bit, participate, and come to class. He was so engaging, funny, uber-smart, and quite handsome. TAKE HIS CLASS!!!
love everything about him!!!

Dr. Paris, as an experience professor/public servant, totally knows his stuff about IR.  His lectures are entertaining, relevant, and informative.  The hardest part of this course was keeping up with the readings - they're pretty long and necessary as a large part of the final was derived from them.  Cute for a prof - has an adorable lisp! :P
Great prof! Very entertaining and knowledgeable about course material. Keep up it the reading and make notes because he uses them in exams. Expect interesting class discussions!

A very thorough professor, but he expects a lot of work and reading out of you. Be sure to stay on top of the text book readings and that you understand them, his exams are strongly based around articles that you've read. A very involved professor, really approachable.

he's very engaging and energetic...very much passionate about the subject matter. He clarifies concepts by giving multiple examples and trying to relate subject matter to current affairs whenever possible. The biggest point to stress is DO THE READINGS...and MAKE NOTES! the material tested on the exam s are HEAVILY derived from reading matetials!

Very engaging lecturer. Knows what he is talking about and makes class interesting as he is very energetic and intelligent. I don't know how old he is but it seems like he is very young for a professor (ie. very bright). He covers concepts with clarity but read the textbook. He covers course material and if you don't read you will not do so well.
he's a good Prof, got his PHD from Yale. hard, but you get to know your**** in the end.
